==Min Nan==
===Etymology===
A slang term originally derived from the middle character of [[е”җеұұдәә]].  [[йҳҝ]] is used to describe a person in the familiar sense.

===Noun===
{{nan-proper|ts|poj=a-soaвҒҝ|pojt=a1soaN1|rs=йҳң05}}
#(''Taiwanese Min Nan'') an old-fashioned term used to describe Chinese people not originally from Taiwan.  This term later came to be replaced by [[еӨ–зңҒдәә]].

